 suggestion or help. We were a little hesitant at first. What is this strange thing Ezboard? Then we warmed to it as we discovered the multiple threads and categories, the image option and endless possibilities for upgrading. <br>
The original Project Orion club was the only place I bothered to spend much time at in the beginning. I rarely visited other messageboards. When members told me we were being attacked and libeled at another forum I took a look and discovered it was true. I answered the condescending insults with factual data from websites. The protagonists didn't understand what Orion was but thought the rival club was a threat to them in some way. One member posted how stupid I must be to think a ship could survive a single big atomic blast pushing it into space. I had to explain that and dozens of other queries. Orion's feasibility is beyond doubt and it would have used many small atomic detonations. Not one. An understandable mistake but these people were trying to put it across to their members that they were all professional rocket scientists. Out of embarassment about me defending my club too well they deleted my messages and continued posting rubbish to their sizable membership to make us look bad. Stating that I had not answered their questions and therefore was a conman. I couldn't respond ofcourse. My posts were deleted instantly. We had done nothing to warrant these attacks remember. Even being called Pedophiles. Just as Atomic pointed out. I'm not certain if I can repeat the other names as children frequent Ezboards too. The tamer ones included Homosexual and Transexual. We were also called Black and Asian. Terms they obviously thought insulting. Another reason these people earned our contempt.<br>
Eventually, perhaps after a year of copping the abuse, the largest clubs at Yahoo space exploration forums got together and ousted them. Then we had a good gloat about it and went back to buisness as usual. That wasn't the end of it ofcourse. There have been other attacks on us. Spamstorms of a scale you wouldn't believe possible and some really devious scams pulled to get us into trouble which mostly backfired. Another reason this place is better. The security is light years ahead of Yahoo. <br>
Among the worst was devious attacks on White Supremacist groups using names similar to our own. A fellow named Cygonaut admitted responsibility for this. He would flame these boards and leave our club address as a calling card. Then we would get foul messages all over our board from neo-nazi's which had to be cleaned up quickly. <br>
Yep, Ezboards is a breath of fresh air. At Yahoo we could ban usernames easily but the pests would return minutes later under an alternate name. Here a users Ip address can be banned.   <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
