Zero. In the first one a junior high math teacher/cheerleading coach* told her principal and her church group in writing that I was a ufo nut and had tried to preach the reality of ufo visitation when I spoke to her class. I had been at the school to talk about critical thinking and the scientific method. Further visits were cancelled on the strength of this deluded crank's word, with nobody having bothered to ask me what was really said. Needless to say, I quickly settled the matter by citing some anti-ufool passages in my newspaper columns and other published work. It was settled out of court.<br>
In an earlier case, a quack who taught &quot;aura-reading&quot; at a local university sued me and my organization because I called her a &quot;quack&quot; in print. This was dismissed, on the apparent grounds that she was a quack. Actually, the judge ruled that this was a fair statement of opinion given the facts as I perceived them and was not, therefore, defamatory.<br>
<br>
*Here in Texas, a cheerleading coach outranks a mere professor any day, so this was obviously an attempt to assert superior status by getting away with defamation.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ubestonnet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bestonnet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fusion Starship Captain</span><br>  Posts: 391<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/24/02 5:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~projectorion/ezboard/posticons/16.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Who We Are: A Little History</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Zero.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
